## Pixel inspection

Used the Inspector tab in GEE to click on individual pixels and read values.

| Pixel location               | NDVI value | What it means            |
| ---------------------------- | ---------- | ------------------------ |
| Dark green area (rice paddy) | 0.64       | Dense healthy vegetation |
| Brown/pink area (river)      | -0.42      | Water body               |

## Why water gives negative NDVI

Water absorbs NIR very strongly and reflects a little Red.
So NIR < Red, which makes (NIR - Red) negative.
Plants do the opposite — they reflect NIR strongly, so NDVI is high and positive.
